DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       This  module  allows  the user to create or modify labels files.  These
       labels files, which are stored in the database, define text information
       for  printing  with _p_._m_a_p and for graphics display with _d_._p_a_i_n_t_._l_a_b_e_l_s.
       Each label has components which determine the text, the location of the
       text on the image, its size, and the background for the text.


       The  interface  is  a  screen-oriented input/edit layout. Each label is
       entered with a single screen. After filling in the required information
       (described  below),  the  user hits to accept the label and start a new
       one. After the last label has been accepted, the user  then  hists  the
       one  more  time  (on an empty label screen) to exit the module and save
       the labels.



